validation_technique: Histology, Ki67 IHC, CD45 IHC, STR analysis
description: The histology of the engrafted tumor retains morphologic features of the primary patient tumor as assessed by a Board Certified Pathologist. IHC for human Ki67 validates that the tumor cells are actively dividing and are of human origin. IHC for CD45 and cytokeratin (AE1/AE3) rules out a xenograft-associated lymphocytic tumor. STR analysis validates provenance of engrafted tumor.

IHC for human Ki67 validates that the tumor cells are actively dividing and are of human origin. IHC for CD45 and cytokeratin (AE1/AE3) rules out a xenograft-associated lymphocytic tumor. STR analysis validates provenance of engrafted tumor.

IHC for human Ki67 validates that the tumor cells are actively dividing and are of human origin. IHC for CD45 and cytokeratin (AE1/AE3) rules out a xenograft-associated lymphocytic tumor. STR analysis validates provenance of engrafted tumor.

IHC for human Ki67 validates that the tumor cells are actively dividing and are of human origin. IHC for CD45 and cytokeratin (AE1/AE3) rules out a xenograft-associated lymphocytic tumor. STR analysis validates provenance of engrafted tumor.
